1 (2) The superintendent of public instruction shall by rule prescribe the method for distribution, the
2 form of the application, budget procedures, and accounting rules for the funds. The legislature intends that the
3 state money be used to enhance distributions of federal funding under the Carl D. Perkins Career and
4 Technical Education Improvement Act of 2006 to support middle grades career and technical education in line
5 with the plan developed under 20-7-330, except that the state money may not be limited by school size and that
6 the distribution method adopted by the superintendent of public instruction be equitable. The superintendent of
7 public instruction may prescribe other requirements for the receipt of funding consistent with Title 20, chapter 7,
8 part 3.
9
10 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Appropriation. (1) There is appropriated $100,000 from the general fund
11 to the office of public instruction for fiscal year 2027 for middle grades career and technical education as
12 described in [section 1].
13 (2) The legislature intends that the appropriation in this section be considered part of the ongoing
14 base for the next legislative session.
15
16 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an
17 integral part of Title 20, chapter 7, part 3, and the provisions of Title 20, chapter 7, part 3, apply to [section 1].
